      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/3/47/12",
      "text": [
        ": \"لاَ يَحْرُمُ مِنَ اَلرَّضَاعِ إِلاَّ مَا كَانَ مَجْبُوراً \" قَالَ قُلْتُ وَ مَا اَلْمَجْبُورُ قَالَ \"أُمٌّ تُرَبِّي أَوْ ظِئْرٌ تُسْتَأْجَرُ أَوْ أَمَةٌ تُشْتَرَى\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.4672 - Hariz narrated from Al-Fudayl ibn Yasar from Abu Abdullah (as) who said: \"Breastfeeding does not create a prohibition except when it is continuous and intentional.\"\nI asked: \"What is meant by continuous and intentional?\"\nImam (as) replied: \"It is when a mother raises the child, a wet nurse is hired, or a bondwoman is purchased for breastfeeding.\""
        ]
      }
    },
